proposed.type: Siamese Capsule Network + Attention + MobileNetV2 Ensemble

dataset.label_strategy: CSV label column (0/1) where 1 means similar.

parameters_definition.name: Ears Region
parameters_definition.definition: Top 20% of detected pet bounding box (proxy for ears/head top).

parameters_definition.name: Eyes Region
parameters_definition.definition: Next 20% band inside the pet bbox (proxy for eyes/upper face).

parameters_definition.name: Muzzle/Snout Region
parameters_definition.definition: Middle 20% band inside the pet bbox (proxy for nose/snout).

parameters_definition.name: Fur/Body Region
parameters_definition.definition: Lower 40% inside the pet bbox (proxy for coat texture/pattern/body shape).

parameters_definition.name: Background
parameters_definition.definition: Pixels outside detected pet bbox (proxy for background reliance / spurious cues).

performance_factors: Background leakage (model attention outside the pet)
Dataset imbalance per breed/label and domain shift vs real uploads
gaps_in_parameters_context: No supervised annotations for explicit parts (ears/eyes/nose). The models learn implicit features; we approximate them using saliency + region aggregation.
Label proxy (breed/name) may differ from real same-pet identity matching; this analysis uses available dataset structure.
BBox is from generic COCO detector; part regions are coarse bands (not true keypoint detection).
architectural_challenges: Siamese similarity relies on thresholding; optimal threshold can drift by scenario (e.g., lowlight).
Capsule/attention models can be harder to interpret than plain CNNs; saliency helps but remains approximate.
Ensembling (custom + MobileNetV2) improves robustness but adds sensitivity to preprocessing differences between branches.
